Package jalds.alds.al.graphs

Contains a collection of graph algorithms.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
FinishedEventObserver Used if we need to be notified when a vertex has been explored in the Depth First Search.
 

Class Summary
BreadthFirstGraphSearch Breadth First Search(BFS) is one of the simplest algorithms for searching a graph, given a graph and a source vertex (s), BFS systematically explores the edges of G to discover every vertex that is reachable from s.
DepthFirstSearch Searches deeper in the graph whenever possible.
DijkstraSingleSourceShortestPath Dijkstra's algorithm solves the single source shortest paths problem on a weighted directed graph G for the case in which all edge weights are non negative.
EulerianPath A Eulerian path is a path in a graph which visits each edge exactly once.A Eulerian circuit is an eulerian path which starts and ends on the same vertex.
StronglyConnectedComponents Finds the strongly connected components in a given directed graph.
TopologicalSort DAG or a directed acyclic graph is a directed graph with no cycles.
TransposeGraphService Used to transpose a directed graph, if a graph has an edge (u,v) the transposed graph will have the edge (v,u)
 

Package jalds.alds.al.graphs Description

Contains a collection of graph algorithms.
